  <entry>
    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/feature-request-flow-function-for-opening-apple-subscription-screen/qaq-p/14020509</id>
    <title>Feature Request: Flow Function for Opening Apple Subscription Screen</title>
    <updated>2025-02-18T19:48:28.329000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>AI2_Marketing</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/1643729</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Hi SAP Build App - Community Team,&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;My name is Denis, and I have been building my application&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&amp;nbsp;on SAP Build App for the past four years. I’ve witnessed incredible improvements since the transition from AppGyver to SAP, and I couldn’t be happier with the platform.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Many friends and colleagues doubted my decision to base my entire development on a low-code platform, warning me that I might regret it. However, SAP Build App and I proved them wrong—I’ve built my solution entirely on this platform.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Currently, there is only one roadblock preventing me from launching my project: Apple requires me to use their subscription system and open the Apple Subscription Management screen,&amp;nbsp;using stripe for Android/Web.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;I have spent the past four weeks searching for a solution—combing through forums, documentation, and Stack Overflow. I even hired iOS developers to help me, but no solution emerged.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;My question is: Is there any chance that SAP Build App could introduce a flow function to open the Apple Subscription Management screen?&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Reference:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;A href="https://developer.apple.com/documentation/storekit/appstore/showmanagesubscriptions(in:)" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer"&gt;Apple Developer Documentation&lt;/A&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;I believe this feature would be a valuable addition to SAP Build App, helping to dispel the misconception that low-code platforms are only suitable for prototypes. It would empower creators like me to launch production-ready applications that meet platform-specific requirements.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Thank you so much for your time and consideration.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Best regards,&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;Denis&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;BR /&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72"&gt;@Dan_Wroblewski&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/107"&gt;@ajmaradiaga&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/4025"&gt;@beapasch&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/feature-request-flow-function-for-opening-apple-subscription-screen/qaq-p/14020509"/>
    <published>2025-02-18T19:48:28.329000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
